 And they run to the train, and they say in Yiddish, &#39;Jews, get down from the train with everything and line up here.&#39; We stepped down."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1454.761","u": "Were these Jewish capos?"},    {"who": "George Kaldore", "start": "1456.506","u": "No, these were not the Jewish capos, but it was a commando [detail] which we later found out was the so-called Canada [??] detail."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1465.684","u": "And what was that?"},    {"who": "George Kaldore", "start": "1466.617","u": "It was the detail which would receive the transport that arrived."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1471.702","u": "Why did they call it the Canada detail?"},    {"who": "George Kaldore", "start": "1473.507","u": "Canada, because they had food which they were stealing from the cars, because they were carrying the things of the Jews from the transports to the storeroom, and there they had plenty to eat."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1489.967","u": "Were they Jews?"},    {"who": "George Kaldore", "start": "1491.240","u": "Yes, yes, they were Jews, deported Jews, who worked in this detail. And they all looked very well because they were eating of that which the transports would bring, what they could still find there. We arrived, and we saw children running around very small children, and mothers and people completely out of their mind, with their hair all tangled and with long beards. Our people from the cars gathered, and they told us to line up and to go into the bath. And there we saw at the lager a large sign on which is written: &#34;WORK MAKES FREE.&#34; We waked over to the gate. There stands an SS chief physician. We later heard and found out the name, Dr. Wengele [??]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1551.590","u": "What happened to him?"},    {"who": "George Kaldore", "start": "1555.111","u": "Happened where?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1555.741","u": "I mean happened now. Was he arrested?"},